HEADWORD: Accordion
<hw>Ac*cor"di*on</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Accord</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A small, portable, keyed
wind instrument, whose tones are generated by play of the wind upon free
metallic reeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

